<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-12T14:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-12T14:30:00-05:00" n="345" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d345">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">733.35/51: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Uruguay (<persName type="from">Wright</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-12T16:00:00-03:30">September
                                    12, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 4:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>53. Diplomatic relations with Argentina resumed today by identic decrees
                            following exchange of notes negotiated by <persName corresp="#p_AJJ1">Amezaga</persName>, confidential agent of Uruguay. Minister for
                            Foreign Affairs who has shown me texts before publication expresses
                            renewed appreciation of our chargé of Uruguayan interests. Texts by
                            mail.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>